{
  "doc_id": "42777",
  "text": "Naturally, the network operations become performance bottlenecks when the underlying network has low bandwidth or long RTT whereas the performance of the local computation operations is bounded by the CPU performance. Lots of previous studies claimed that there are two possible sources of performance bottlenecks for web page loading operations over mobile network. One is poor network performance [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] , and the other is limited CPU capability [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] . However, the improvement in web page loading time from reducing the amount of computation is marginal in current smartphone systems [CITATION_8] .",
